{{climate chart | [[Bilbao]] | 4.7 | 13.2 | 126 | 5.1 | 14.5 | 97 | 5.7 | 15.9 | 94 | 7.1 | 16.8 | 124 | 10.1 | 20.1 | 90 | 12.6 | 22.6 | 64 | 14.8 | 25.2 | 62 | 15.2 | 25.5 | 82 | 13.2 | 24.4 | 74 | 10.8 | 20.8 | 121 | 7.6 | 16.4 | 141 | 6.0 | 14.0 | 116 |float=right |source=[[World Meteorological Organization|WMO]]<ref name="WMO">[http://www.worldweather.org/083/c01233.htm World Weather Information Service - Bilbao] - World Meteorological Organization</ref>}} [[Bilbao]] and its metropolitan area has an [[oceanic climate]] according to the [[Köppen climate classification]] ('' Cfb'')<ref name=KGcc>{{Cite journal|author=M. Kottek|author2=J. Grieser |author3=C. Beck |author4=B. Rudolf |author5=F. Rubel |title=World Map of the Köppen-Geiger climate classification updated|journal=Meteorol. Z.|volume=15|pages=259–263|url=http://koeppen-geiger.vu-wien.ac.at/pics/kottek_et_al_2006.gif|doi=10.1127/0941-2948/2006/0130|accessdate=22 April 2009|year=2006|bibcode = 2006MetZe..15..259K }}</ref> with mild winters and warm summers. According to the Troll-Paffen climate classification, Bilbao has a [[temperate climate]]<ref>[http://web.tiscali.it/linnets/Troll-Paffen.jpg Climatic map by Istituto Geografico De Agostini, according to Troll-Paffen climate classification] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121004052732/http://web.tiscali.it/linnets/Troll-Paffen.jpg |date=October 4, 2012 }}</ref> and according to the Siegmund/Frankenberg climate classification, Bilbao has a [[Subtropics|subtropical climate]].<ref>[http://www.ph-heidelberg.de/geographie/forschung-und-entwicklung/klimakarte-der-erde.html ''Die Klimatypen der Erde''] - Pädagogische Hochschule in [[Heidelberg]]</ref> According to the [[European Environment Agency]], Bilbao lies within the [[Atlantic Ocean|Atlantic]] [[biogeography|biogeographical]] region.<ref>Europe's environment: the third assessment. Environmental assessment report No 10. European Environment Agency, Luxembourg: Office for Official Publications of the European Communities, p. 231 ([[:File:Europe biogeography countries.svg|map]])</ref> The climate of Bilbao and the rest of the north-western part of Spain (the so-called [[Green Spain]]) is different from the rest of the country, characterized by a higher amount of rainfall and precipitation days, fewer sunshine hours and mild temperatures, in summer comparable to northern half of Europe with temperate climate.
== Temperatures == {| class="infobox bordered" style="text-align:center" |- !Yearly max temp !Yearly mean temp !Yearly min temp |- class="mergedrow" |19.1&nbsp;°C |14.3&nbsp;°C |9.4&nbsp;°C |} Said proximity to the ocean also makes that the two most defined seasons (summer and winter) remain mild, with low intensity thermal oscillations. Its average annual temperature is 19.1&nbsp;°C during the day and 9.4&nbsp;°C at night. In the coldest month – January, typically the temperature is around 13-14&nbsp;°C during the day and 5&nbsp;°C at night. In the warmest month – August, the typically temperature is around 25-26&nbsp;°C during the day and about 15&nbsp;°C at night.<ref name="AEMET" />
== Precipitation == Bilbao has on average 128 precipitation days a year, therein average few to dozen rainy days per month (≥ 1&nbsp;mm), ranging from 7 in July to 13 in January. The average annual precipitation is 1195&nbsp;mm, ranging from 62&nbsp;mm in July to 141&nbsp;mm in November.<ref name="AEMET" /> This is one of the highest results in Spain, like the rest of Green Spain and Bay of Biscay area. Precipitation in the region is abundant, and given the latitude and atmospheric dynamics, rainy days represent 45% and cloudy days 40% of the annual total.<ref name="Geografía de Euskal Herria">Geografía de Euskal Herria: Vizcaya - Gómez Piñeiro, Francisco Javier; San Sebastián 1979 {{ISBN|84-7407-068-6}}</ref>
{{Weather box |location= Bilbao <small>(precipitation days – 1&nbsp;mm)</small> |metric first= yes |single line= yes |Jan precipitation mm = 120 |Feb precipitation mm = 86 |Mar precipitation mm = 90 |Apr precipitation mm = 107 |May precipitation mm = 78 |Jun precipitation mm = 60 |Jul precipitation mm = 50 |Aug precipitation mm = 76 |Sep precipitation mm = 73 |Oct precipitation mm = 111 |Nov precipitation mm = 147 |Dec precipitation mm = 122 |year precipitation mm = 1134 |Jan precipitation days = 13 |Feb precipitation days = 11 |Mar precipitation days = 11 |Apr precipitation days = 13 |May precipitation days = 11 |Jun precipitation days = 7 |Jul precipitation days = 7 |Aug precipitation days = 8 |Sep precipitation days = 8 |Oct precipitation days = 11 |Nov precipitation days = 13 |Dec precipitation days = 12 |year precipitation days = 124 |unit precipitation days= 1&nbsp;mm |source 1= [[Agencia Estatal de Meteorología]]<ref name="AEMET" /> |date=September 2013}}
