== Humidity == Average [[relative humidity]] is 72%, ranging from 70% in February and March to 74% in August and November.<ref name="AEMET" />
{{Weather box |location = Bilbao |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jan humidity = 72 |Feb humidity = 69 |Mar humidity = 68 |Apr humidity = 69 |May humidity = 69 |Jun humidity = 70 |Jul humidity = 71 |Aug humidity = 72 |Sep humidity = 71 |Oct humidity = 71 |Nov humidity = 73 |Dec humidity = 72 |year humidity = 70 |source 1 = [[Agencia Estatal de Meteorología]]<ref name="AEMET" /> |date=September 2013}}
== Snow == [[Snow]] is not frequent in the city, while it is possible to see snow on the top of the surrounding mountains. City recorded to few snow days per year. In February 1956 reported record: 7 of snow days in the month.<ref name="AEMET-extremes"/> [[Rain and snow mixed|Sleet]] is more frequent, about 10 days per year, mainly in the winter months.<ref name="Geografía de Euskal Herria"/>
{{Weather box |location = Bilbao |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jan snow days = 0.7 |Feb snow days = 0.7 |Mar snow days = 0.3 |Apr snow days = 0 |May snow days = 0 |Jun snow days = 0 |Jul snow days = 0 |Aug snow days = 0 |Sep snow days = 0 |Oct snow days = 0 |Nov snow days = 0.1 |Dec snow days = 0.3 |year snow days = 2.2 |source 1 = [[Agencia Estatal de Meteorología]]<ref name="AEMET" /> |date=September 2013}}
== Daylight == Bilbao enjoys one of the most optimal number of hours of daylight in Europe. Days in winter are not as short as in the northern part of the continent, the average hours of daylight in December, January and February is 9.66 hours<ref name=weather2travel /> (for comparison: [[London]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/united-kingdom/london.php</ref> or [[Moscow]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/russia-europe/moscow.php</ref> or [[Warsaw]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/poland/warsaw.php</ref> - about 8 hours). {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;" |+Average hours of daylight<ref name=weather2travel /> |- ! Hours ! Jan ! Feb ! Mar ! Apr ! May ! Jun ! Jul ! Aug ! Sep ! Oct ! Nov ! Dec |- ! Day | 9 | 11 | 12 | 13 | 15 | 15 | 15 | 14 | 12 | 11 | 10 | 9 |- ! Twilight/Night | 15 | 13 | 12 | 11 | 9 | 9 | 9 | 10 | 12 | 13 | 14 | 15 |}
== Sunshine == [[Sunshine duration]] is 1,584 hours per year, from 78 - average above 2.5 hours of sunshine at day in December to 188 - average above 6 hours of sunshine at day in July.<ref name="AEMET">{{cite web |url=http://www.aemet.es/en/serviciosclimaticos/datosclimatologicos/valoresclimatologicos?l=1082&k=pva |title=Standard Climate Values. Bilbao Aeropuerto}}</ref> This is similar result (range of 1,200-2,000 hours) which is recorded in the northern half of Europe, for example: London, Warsaw; but in winter Bilbao has about two times more sun duration than in the northern half of Europe. The city has up to two times less sunshine duration than other Spanish cities besides [[Green Spain]] area.
{{Weather box |location = Bilbao |Jand sun = 2.77 |Febd sun = 3.46 |Mard sun = 4.12 |Aprd sun = 4.26 |Mayd sun = 5.16 |Jund sun = 5.76 |Juld sun = 6.06 |Augd sun = 5.77 |Sepd sun = 5.23 |Octd sun = 3.96 |Novd sun = 3.10 |Decd sun = 2.51 |yeard sun = |Jan sun= 86 |Feb sun= 97 |Mar sun= 128 |Apr sun= 128 |May sun= 160 |Jun sun= 173 |Jul sun= 188 |Aug sun= 179 |Sep sun= 157 |Oct sun= 123 |Nov sun= 93 |Dec sun= 78 |year sun= 1584 |source 1 = [[Agencia Estatal de Meteorología]]<ref name="AEMET" /> |date=September 2013}}
== Temperature extremes == The highest temperature ever recorded during the day in the city centre is 42&nbsp;°C on 26 July 1947. In the month of August 2003, the average reported daytime maximum temperature was a record 29.9&nbsp;°C. The coldest temperature ever recorded was -8.6&nbsp;°C on the night of 3 February 1963.<ref name="AEMET-extremes">[http://www.aemet.es/en/-s:pdf/serviciosclimaticos/datosclimatologicos/efemerides_extremos*?w=0&k=pva&l=1082&datos=det&x=1082&m=13&v=todos (pdf)][http://www.aemet.es/en/-s:pdf/serviciosclimaticos/datosclimatologicos/efemerides_extremos*?w=0&k=pva&l=1082&datos=det&x=1082&m=13&v=todos www version] - Extreme Values. Bilbao Aeropuerto - Agencia Estatal de Meteorología</ref>
