Prof. '''Diogo José Brochado de Abreu''' (born 24 July 1947, [[Alguber]]) is a Portuguese geographer.
After his basic and secondary education at [[Colégio Militar]], he graduated in geography in 1978 at the Faculty of Humanities of the [[University of Lisbon]], where he also took a Doctorate in Geography in 1989.<ref name=CEG>{{cite web|url=http://www.ceg.ul.pt/investigadores.asp?id=11|title=Diogo José Brochado de Abreu|work=Centro de Estudos Geográficos da Universidade de Lisboa|date=2009-05-11|accessdate=2009-06-17}}</ref>
He is known for his research, teaching and consulting activities,<ref name=rebides>{{cite web|url=http://www.rebides.oces.mctes.pt/Rebides01/rebid_m3.asp?CodD=1398&CodP=0704 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007191450/http://www.rebides.oces.mctes.pt/Rebides01/rebid_m3.asp?CodD=1398&CodP=0704 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2011-10-07 |title=Lista de Pessoal Docente ao abrigo do Decreto-Lei n.º 15/96, de 6 de Março |year=2001 |accessdate=2009-06-17 }}</ref> besides having been President of the Portuguese Speleological Federation. He is currently the Director of the Centre for Geographical Studies of the University of Lisbon.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ceg.ul.pt/apresentacao.asp?id=1|title=Mensagem do Director|work=Centro de Estudos Geogr&aacute;ficos|year=2007|accessdate=2009-06-17}}</ref>
26 of his academic publications are listed on the University of Lisbon website.<ref name=CEG />
==Qualifications==
*2006 - Agregação em Geografia, Universidade de Lisboa *1989 - Doutoramento em Geografia Humana, Faculdade de Letras, Universidade de Lisboa *1978 - Licenciatura em Geografia, Faculdade de Letras, Universidade de Lisboa
