The '''Jose P. Laurel Highway''', is a {{convert|49|km|mi|adj=on}}, two-to-six lane, primary highway, designated as a component part of the '''National Route 4''' ('''N4'''), running within the province of [[Batangas]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2017%20DPWH%20ATLAS/Road%20Data%202016/batangas_2nd.htm|title=Batangas 2nd|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-06-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2017%20DPWH%20ATLAS/Road%20Data%202016/batangas_3rd.htm|title=Batangas 3rd|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-06-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2017%20DPWH%20ATLAS/Road%20Data%202016/batangas_4th.htm|title=Batangas 4th|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-06-08}}</ref> The [[Southern Tagalog Arterial Road]] mostly parallels the highway, and crosses each other at [[Lipa, Batangas|Lipa]]. The highway includes a short bypass route over the ''[[poblacion]]'' of Santo Tomas, that spurs from the main highway and joins Maharlika Highway at Santo Tomas Junction.

The highway is named in honor to the [[President of the Philippines|President]] of the [[Second Philippine Republic]], [[Jose P. Laurel]].

