{{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Papua New Guinea | country_link = Papua New Guinea | continent = Oceania | map_image = Papua New Guinea (orthographic projection).svg | map_caption = | map_size = 200px | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +675 | international_prefix = 00 | trunk_prefix = None | regulator = | plan_membership = | nsn_length = | plan_type = | number_format = | codes_list = }}
'''Telephone numbers in [[Papua New Guinea]]''' consist of a eight digit national number, which is used for fixed, mobile and special rate services. There are no access codes for trunk services.
International dialling format: +675 NXX XX XXX
The international prefix for Papua New Guinea was changed from ‘05’ to ’00’ in 2010.
